<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="357" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6354/220: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-15">May 15,
                                    1940</date>.<lb/>[Received May 15—2:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1220. The Colonial Office states that it has seen American newspaper
                                reports to the effect that Mr. Hopkins<note n="53" xml:id="d357fn53">Harry Hopkins, Secretary of Commerce until September
                                    1940.</note> is looking into the tin situation with a view to
                                increasing American stocks; it pointed out that the next meeting of
                                the Tin Committee would be on May 27 and that if American Government
                                purchases are to be made it would be one of the relevant factors to
                                be taken into consideration at that meeting. The Colonial Office
                                indicated it would accordingly appreciate being advised prior to the
                                meeting if there is any intention to make such purchases.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>